  "text": "In [CITATION_1] the cost matrix is encoded differently on a distance (HEOM distance) of node signatures. A signature describes the node (degree, attributes), the incident edges attributes but also the degrees of the adjacent nodes. The main differences with the previous approach is that no prior computation (learning phase) of the edit cost function are needed and more global information are taken into account on the graph in the signature.",
